{
  "updated_summary": "A man in a white t-shirt and patterned swim trunks surfaces from turquoise ocean waters holding a large conch shell, exclaiming \"Oh, yes! Got another one. That's huge!\" He presents it to Miko, a man in a black shirt and colorful headband, who excitedly examines the shell, noting its slipperiness and calling it \"a beast\" with a market value of \"30.\" The scene shifts to the boat’s interior where Miko and a man in a red shirt are seated with conch shells; Miko questions if a shell is a \"medium-sized conch\" and observes, \"Oh, it peed,\" which the man in red clarifies is \"just water.\" The man in red explains they call it a \"helmet queen because it's shaped like a helmet.\" An upbeat acoustic music track begins as a narrator explains the \"sea helmet\" is a giant mollusk and that \"Bahamians don't eat it.\" A surreal montage follows, featuring a woman on a bicycle with a conch shell on her head and a close-up of a hot pot dish with conch. The final scene shows Miko, now in a red bandana and floral shirt, at a restaurant table eating from a hot pot, while a close-up of a conch shell’s interior is shown again, transitioning from the sea to an urban restaurant environment. The video then shows a close-up of a cooked conch shell, transitioning to a kitchen where a man in a red bandana and floral shirt handles a conch. On a boat, Miko and the man in the red shirt discuss eating conch raw, with the man in red detailing the cleaning process, including removing the \"poop sack\" and \"thick skin\" to reveal \"clean, delicious-looking white meat.\" He mentions they \"scorch it up a little bit.\" Miko eats raw conch, describing it as \"crispy, sweet,\" \"kind of dense, almost like an abalone,\" and \"super fresh and it has some natural oceanic sweetness.\""
